  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dd4. 50\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0da2\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Bread Rs. It will be reduced by 50 if the government supports it",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "If the government and related authorities provide necessary support to the bakery owners, the price of a pound of bread can be reduced by 50 rupees and the price of other bakery products can be reduced to a significant level and the people can be relieved, said the President of All Lanka Bakery Owners' Association N.K. Mr. Jayawardena announced today (22nd) while calling a press conference at Mr. A's office in Raddolaugama.",
        "There, he emphasized that the price of flour, sugar, margarine and eggs, the main ingredients required for bakery production, has greatly increased, so if the bakery owners are given that advantage, they can reduce the price of bread, which has become unbearably expensive for the people today.",
        "Mr. Jayawardena said that due to the dollar issue, the price of bakery products in the market has increased greatly in the Sri Lankan market and stated that a bread mafia is also operating in the country.",
        "They also said that the bakery owners had to get bread for 280 rupees due to the mafia for 200 rupees. He also said that the price of eggs has also increased unfairly, and even though the government has imposed a control price on eggs, eggs are not available in the market at the control price. Mr. Jayawardena had stated that if the government and authorities support, the price of 400 grams of bread, which is high at 190 rupees, can be reduced by 50 rupees, a bun sold at a price of 100 rupees by 25 rupees, and the price of other bakery products can be reduced by a significant amount. He also emphasized that if the government does not intervene and provide support to this problem, there may be a referendum in the country not to buy bakery products, just as there was a referendum in the country not to eat biscuits."
      ],
